description: We are one of 12 regional Reserve Banks that, along with the Board of Governors in Washington, D.C., make up the Federal Reserve System. Together, we work to ensure the strength and integrity of the U.S. economy and financial system and create the conditions that generate jobs, promote stable prices, and foster economic growth. At the Philadelphia Fed, we help shape the nation’s monetary policy, supervise and regulate financial institutions, support the safe and efficient operation of the U.S. payments and financial system, and promote fair and impartial access to credit and inclusive growth.
name: Federal Reserve Bank of Philadelphia
